Ukraine: 

"We need serious negotiations for peace, based on the principles of the United Nations Charter."

@antonioguterres urges Security Council to do everything in its power to end the war &amp; mitigate its impact. https://t.co/i6jINU34Mx https://t.co/2VMkWxj0CE

Women are among those most affected by the climate crisis, but they also have unique knowledge &amp; experience

@UN_Women has more about why they need to be at the heart of #ClimateAction. 
https://t.co/YAiRxZVA7l

Before the war, Ukraine was one of the breadbaskets of the world. 

Today, the consequences of the conflict are triggering a wave of collateral hunger across the globe.

@WFP explains what this mean for millions of vulnerable people. https://t.co/dFYFnkcLkf

The war in Ukraine has forced millions of children from their homes &amp; communities.

@UNESCO is helping students to continue learning by supporting teachers and providing computers &amp; digital education tools to young refugees.

https://t.co/aWUpzDQSN6

147 million children have missed more than half of their in-person schooling over the past two years. 

@UNICEF says we must get students back to their classrooms &amp; provide them with the support they need to catch up.
https://t.co/QopOp3KkTn

To avert a climate catastrophe, we need bold pledges matched by concrete #ClimateAction. 

@antonioguterres launches expert group for stronger &amp; clearer standards for net-zero emissions commitments.  
https://t.co/jNfFChu39M https://t.co/dp6OgThb1F

As the war in Ukraine continues, food insecurity is becoming an increasing concern. 

@WFP has reached 1 million people inside the country with life-saving food aid.

More on efforts to support the most vulnerable: https://t.co/aDSS3jl6hb https://t.co/qq3MisNNRv

Millions of children around the 🌍 go to school on an empty stomach, which affects their ability to learn.

@WFP's school meals aim to improve children's health &amp; promote school attendance. Here's an example from South Sudan 👇 https://t.co/Ri4U6jXPFp  

https://t.co/IjFH2VrYtk

The Champions of the Earth award honours individuals, groups &amp; organizations whose actions have a transformative impact on the environment.

@UNEP explains how you can nominate your #EarthChamps for 2022.
https://t.co/T3Bx6OJudi
